        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="29"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <head>29. Telegram 320 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d29fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–555. Confidential. Repeated to
                        Bonn as telegram 46.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-05"
                            >August 5, 1955, 4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d29-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d29-1"/>
                <p>320. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Bonn’s 413 to Dept
                    repeated Geneva 38.</p>
                <p>FYI. Have seen Feine several times and as last year have confidentially given him
                    general information on talks on civilians on basis German interest German
                    civilians in China. When discussion “other practical problems” reached hope
                    arrangements such Germans will receive all info thru Dept and Bonn.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
